---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Features - Echo4Ever" description="Six ways to preserve your memories: Life Story, Family Tree, Photographs, Videos & Audio, Documents and Time Capsules.">

  <section class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Everything you need to preserve a life</h1>
      <p>Six tools. One vault. Complete control over who sees what and when.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Life Story -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="feature-detail">
        <div class="feature-detail__content">
          <h2><svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 12px;"><path d="M12 20h9"/><path d="M16.5 3.5a2.121 2.121 0 013 3L7 19l-4 1 1-4L16.5 3.5z"/></svg>Life Story</h2>
          <p>Not every memory is a photo. Some of the most powerful moments live in words. Echo4Ever gives you a space to write about your childhood, the lessons you've learned, the people who shaped you and the experiences that made you who you are.</p>
          <p>Not sure where to start? Our gentle prompts are here to help:</p>
          <blockquote class="prompt-quotes">
            <p><em>"What's your earliest childhood memory?"</em></p>
            <p><em>"What tradition do you want your family to carry on?"</em></p>
            <p><em>"What's the best advice you were ever given?"</em></p>
          </blockquote>
          <p>Think of them as conversation starters - between you and the future. No pressure. No word count. Just your story, in your own voice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Family Tree -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="feature-detail">
        <div class="feature-detail__content">
          <h2><svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 12px;"><path d="M17 21v-2a4 4 0 00-4-4H5a4 4 0 00-4 4v2"/><circle cx="9" cy="7" r="4"/><path d="M23 21v-2a4 4 0 00-3-3.87"/><path d="M16 3.13a4 4 0 010 7.75"/></svg>Family Tree</h2>
          <p>Map out the people who made you. Parents, grandparents, siblings, children - your family tree is a living picture of where you come from and who you're connected to.</p>
          <p>Add names, relationships, and details as you go. It doesn't need to be complete on day one. Fill in what you know now and add more as you discover it - or as your family grows.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Photographs -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="feature-detail">
        <div class="feature-detail__content">
          <h2><svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 12px;"><rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2" ry="2"/><circle cx="8.5" cy="8.5" r="1.5"/><polyline points="21 15 16 10 5 21"/></svg>Photographs</h2>
          <p>The photos that tell your story deserve a proper home. Upload family portraits, holiday snaps, school photos, wedding albums - anything worth holding onto.</p>
          <p>Organise them by decade, by event, or by the people in them. Add a caption to remember the details that might otherwise fade. That blurry photo from 1974? It might be the most important one you have.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Videos & Audio -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="feature-detail">
        <div class="feature-detail__content">
          <h2><svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 12px;"><polygon points="23 7 16 12 23 17 23 7"/><rect x="1" y="5" width="15" height="14" rx="2" ry="2"/></svg>Videos &amp; Audio</h2>
          <p>Some moments are best captured in motion and sound. A video of your child's first steps. A recording of your grandmother singing her favourite song. Your own voice, telling a story in a way that words on a page never could.</p>
          <p>Upload videos and audio recordings and keep them safe alongside everything else in your archive.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Documents -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="feature-detail">
        <div class="feature-detail__content">
          <h2><svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 12px;"><path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/><polyline points="14 2 14 8 20 8"/><line x1="16" y1="13" x2="8" y2="13"/><line x1="16" y1="17" x2="8" y2="17"/><polyline points="10 9 9 9 8 9"/></svg>Documents</h2>
          <p>The paperwork of a life matters more than most people think. Birth certificates, handwritten letters, recipes passed down through generations, military records, old newspaper clippings - these are the pieces that fill in the gaps.</p>
          <p>Upload and store them safely, organised however makes sense to you. They'll be right there when someone needs them - whether that's tomorrow or decades from now.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Time Capsules -->
  <section class="section section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="feature-detail">
        <div class="feature-detail__content">
          <h2><svg width="32" height="32" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="var(--color-accent)" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="vertical-align: middle; margin-right: 12px;"><rect x="2" y="7" width="20" height="14" rx="2" ry="2"/><path d="M16 21V5a2 2 0 00-2-2h-4a2 2 0 00-2 2v16"/><line x1="12" y1="11" x2="12" y2="17"/><line x1="9" y1="14" x2="15" y2="14"/></svg>Time Capsules</h2>
          <p>Some things are worth waiting for. Seal a memory, set a date and let Echo4Ever keep it safe until the right moment arrives.</p>
          <p>A message for your son's 18th birthday. A photo album unlocked on your wedding anniversary. A piece of wisdom revealed exactly when it's needed most.</p>
          <p>Until that date arrives, it stays sealed - even from you. It's your way of reaching into the future and being there for the moments that matter, even when you can't be.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Sharing & Legacy -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2>Share on your terms</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary" style="margin: 0 auto 48px;">
        Every memory starts completely private. Sharing is always a conscious choice - never an accident.
      </p>
      <div class="grid grid--3">
        <div class="card text-center">
          <h3>Family Sharing</h3>
          <p class="text-secondary">Invite people to view the memories you choose. They can only ever see what you've specifically shared - nothing more.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <h3>Time-Locked Delivery</h3>
          <p class="text-secondary">Lock a memory, set a date. Echo4Ever delivers it when the time is right. Until then, it stays sealed - even from you.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card text-center">
          <h3>Heritage Custodian</h3>
          <p class="text-secondary">Appoint someone you trust. When the time comes, the memories you've chosen are gently shared. Exactly as you intended.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="cta-banner section--alt">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Start building your archive</h2>
      <p>You don't need to do it all at once. Add a single photo today. Write a paragraph next week. Your archive grows with you.</p>
      <a href="https://app.echo4ever.com/signup" class="btn btn--primary btn--large">Get Started</a>
    </div>
  </section>

</Base>

<style>
  .feature-detail {
    max-width: 100%;
    margin: 0;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .feature-detail__content {
    max-width: 100%;
  }

  .feature-detail__content p {
    font-size: clamp(18px, 2vw, 24px);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .feature-detail h2 {
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }

  .prompt-quotes {
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-accent);
    padding-left: 20px;
    margin: 16px 0;
  }

  .prompt-quotes p {
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
  }
</style>
